The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 November is 106,513 (12,276.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 November, there were 4,994 new confirmed cases (575.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 November, there were 3,851 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 30% (1,143 extra cases).
